I think Wall Street is well aware of the broader direction it needs to take, said former JPMorgan investment banker Douglas Elliott.
The problem is in the details, he added.
The Goldman Sachs bank has become the target of criticism after it set aside nearly $17 billion (almost CZK 300 billion) for bonuses in the first three quarters of this year.
According to Reuters, the total amount of remuneration in the company for this year will probably exceed 20 billion dollars, despite the measure announced today.
High remuneration in the banking sector has become a hot political issue in many countries with the advent of the financial crisis.
Britain announced on Wednesday that it intends to impose a one-time fifty percent tax on bankers&#39; bonuses exceeding 25,000 pounds (roughly CZK 712,000).
France is also preparing similar steps.
