Morgan Freeman played Mandela in Clint Eastwood&#39;s new movie
South Africans say the new Hollywood film Invictus: The Undefeated will tell the world a lot about the country, its struggles and victories despite some criticism that American actors are playing the lead roles.
The story tells about sports, race relations and Nelson Mandela.
The tireless fighter against the racist apartheid regime in the Republic of South Africa and its first black president, Nelson Mandela, is represented in his life story by Oscar-winning American actor Morgan Freeman.
Freeman said the 91-year-old Mandela asked him if he could play him in Eastwood&#39;s film.
