The mystery of the glow over Norway solved: the Russians tested a missile
A strange light effect of unknown origin could be observed over Norway.
Only yesterday, the Russian Ministry of Defense admitted that it had tested an intercontinental ballistic missile near the Norwegian border.
But the launch was unsuccessful again, and the missile known as the &quot;Bulava&quot; type, which was originally supposed to be the pride of the Russian army, is slowly becoming a nightmare for Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir Putin.
Even his repeated presence during rocket tests had no effect on the success of the test flights.
