Vaccination against pneumococci will be free and optional
Vaccination against pneumococci from January will break old habits.
It should be the first for families to be free and at the same time optional.
But voices are already being heard that mandatory vaccination would be more effective.
Preparations for the introduction of free vaccination against pneumococci are at their peak.
The Institute of Medicine already sets the maximum prices for vaccines that health insurance companies will pay.
