Just yesterday, Ganvam reminded again that special attention needs to be paid to the management of these vehicles as well as industrial vehicles (trucks and buses).
The dealers&#39; association assumes that the development in 2010 will be similar to last year and, according to calculations, sales of passenger cars and 4x4s will drop by 19%.
An auxiliary system for the handbrake is already mandatory equipment.
As in the case of the ABS anti-lock system, it will also include ESP stability control, auxiliary handbrake systems, all of which will become mandatory equipment for European cars.
In fact, it already forms part of the mandatory equipment of all newly registered passenger cars and light commercial vehicles, while for others the deadline for eliminating the deficiency is set, which is February 2011.
The measure introduced in the EU aims to increase the protection of pedestrians, while it works in such a way that it can help prevent many collisions.
The handbrake assist system increases the pressure on the brakes in an emergency, which the system detects after the driver depresses the pedal.
But he can&#39;t always sustain this pressure until the end.
According to a study by auto parts manufacturer Bosch, a third of drivers involved in an accident did not hit their brakes before a crash, and half of them did not use their full brake force.
Up to 1,100 accidents
On the contrary, this assistance requires the maximum from the braking system, it shortens the braking distance of the vehicle.
According to a study carried out in the EU itself, if all vehicles were equipped with this type of device, up to 1,100 fatal accidents involving pedestrians could be avoided each year.
The reduction of this number will be even more striking - according to calculations, one out of four accidents with an impact on persons would be prevented - after the introduction of so-called intelligent handbrake systems.
In this case, the vehicle will be equipped with a system that (using radar or a camera) detects obstacles and reports them to the driver, in addition to light braking.
If the driver reacts, it will help him increase the pressure on the pedal if needed.
If the driver does not react, even if the collision cannot be avoided, the device applies the brake as intensively as possible and reduces the risk of damage to a minimum.
