New tools for car valuation
In these days of storms and accidents, not only car repair shops make money.
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered an insurance event are towed to a service center where an expert must estimate the damage and repair costs.
No two claims are the same, and calculating the cost of parts and labor time can be a long and complicated job.
It can take two or three hours to manually calculate the cost of a repair from 20,000 to 30,000 euros, including parts and labor.
However, with the support of new computer tools, it would be a matter of minutes
Therefore, almost 100% of experts use this kind of system.
Claims and maintenance estimating services and solutions providers are dedicated to collecting information provided by manufacturers in order to develop and offer a useful tool to their customers.
In Spain, Audatex, from the American Solera group, is the leading company; 80% of the reviews are done with its products.
Other companies competing in the field of valuation and sector intelligence tools are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with data provided by manufacturers is not easy at all.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, they work with 63 manufacturers and importers in Spain, and each of them provides them with information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to process continues to grow, as more versions, variants and engine solutions have been introduced in the last five years than in the previous fifteen years.
As soon as a new vehicle enters the market, these businesses go to work.
It is a very hectic job as each of the thousands of vehicle parts must be cataloged and priced.
In addition, &quot;intelligent&quot; graphic processing&quot; is carried out for each model, where it is possible to &quot;punch out&quot; individual parts of touring cars.
For a model with massive sales, the job can be done in a week if the process is very fast.
For a minor car, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
The most exclusive models they have information on include Porsches, but not Ferraris or Lamborghinis, for example.
Regarding the rolling stock, they exceed 99%.
To carry out the work of documenting and developing databases, Audatex has eight centers distributed around the world (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in specific brands.
The national headquarters is in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (normally mechanical experts) work simultaneously on three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million euros per year in developing these databases.
2.5 million entries are entered each month and customers receive updates every two days.
Processing this immense stream of information enables businesses to make different uses and deliver different products.
The most common uses are focused on repairs and maintenance, but depending on the country, there are also tools for managing spare parts or calculating the sale or residual value of the car.
The only company that has a guide that informs about the value of used vehicles in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer them in our country, but they do in the United States.
With the products that Audatex offers, it is easy to get support that can be used by professionals in the sector.
The business offers ten different tools, with the star product being AudaPlus, a standard claims valuation solution for connoisseurs.
It includes cars, motorcycles and light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of parts, it also includes the repair time estimated by the manufacturer or paint shop.
This tool is pay-as-you-go for each assessment.
The highest price is 5.75 euros for customers who use it little, no more than ten times a month.
Then each insurance company, which carries out thousands of estimates, negotiates its price with Audatex.
Other products such as AudaVIN enable complete identification of the vehicle and the equipment it came with off the assembly line based on just the first chassis number.
AudaGlass focuses on vehicle glass, and AudaSubastas is an open service to the professional sector on the Internet that allows you to scrap vehicles with a total insurance claim.
Its statistical service is very useful for identifying trends, performing geodemographic analysis or finding variations by brand or model.
For example, it is possible to study how many models of a certain brand have been serviced due to an accident or how many have suffered serious insurance events during a certain period.
Gt Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of tools.
Among other things, it sells Gt Estimate, which is also intended for connoisseurs and likewise provides digital images, access to parts or prices, and official manufacturer times.
Gt Motive is an Einsa Group company founded in 1971 as a supplier of automotive damage, accident or maintenance assessment services and solutions
Gt Guía Valuation is its benchmark historical product on the market.
They work with 24,000 service users, 3,100 experts and 53 insurance companies.
Turnover has grown by 20% annually over the past three years and in 2008 they billed 10.8 million euros.
At the beginning of last year, the process of internationalization began with the installation of an office in Paris.
Audatex was founded in Germany in 1966 and established itself in Spain in 1979.
According to company sources, 62% of its brother is produced in Europe and 38% in North and South America. It works with 900 insurance companies and 33,000 services, of which 3,000 are in Spain.
The global turnover of the Solera group (Audatex, Sidexa, Informex ABZ, Hollander and IMS) will reach 557 million dollars, which is 3.3% more than in 2008.
In our country, the company earns 19.1 million euros, which is 7.2% more than last year.
In 2005, the Solera group was worth 1,000 million dollars on the stock exchange, and now its shares are estimated at a total value of 2,400 million dollars.
It has been listed on the New York Stock Exchange since 2007 and is included in the Standard &amp; Poor&#39;s benchmark index.
Online auction of crashed vehicles
Last October, the Solera group bought Autoonline, an internet base for the sale of cars and motorcycles or special vehicles after an insurance event.
The operation assumed the subscription of 59.5 million euros from 85% of the company&#39;s capital, which could be expanded next year by the remaining 15%.
The aim of the purchase was to provide more value-added services to customers with access to a huge international market.
This service of valuation and purchase and sale is guaranteed exclusively to professionals in the sector such as insurance companies, experts, rental companies, repair shops, sales of spare parts and professional sellers, who must register before starting operations.
This platform was established in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650,000 operations throughout Europe, of which 500,000 in Germany.
Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey stand out among the main markets.
The website currently has more than 1,500 registered sellers and 4,000 experts.
It manages 3,000 daily ads and about 100 new ads are added to the Spanish market every day.
According to Spanish law, a car whose chassis number has been retired cannot return to service, but can be used as a source of spare parts that have not been damaged.
Cars with historical value may be allowed to operate, although they have been scrapped, after preliminary control.
Service budget in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex guarantees that the user gets a budget in just four steps: vehicle identification, spare part search, budget creation and budget generation.
Ease of use is an essential condition for these systems, especially for the conviction of older professionals who tend to be more or less reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database contains 1,034 vehicles, of which 666 are tourist, 109 off-road, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Naturally, you need a computer with an Internet connection to use it.
After identifying the model to be repaired using the chassis number, a real graphical representation of the model will appear and then the necessary spare part will be selected.
The user can include variables such as labor cost, surcharges or discounts, then print and give to the customer.
AudaTaller is not a valuation tool like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalog.
The main difference between the two systems is that it is service oriented and does not involve manpower estimation.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is 350 euros per year, which can be financed by the customer.
Audatex is currently working on making these displays three-dimensional.
This is an innovation that mechanics welcome, as it will allow, for example, a door to be selected and rotated to reveal the inside.
